-I'm at the gym.

250
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:23,400
Are you in the dormitory?

251
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,760
Are you training a lot these days?

252
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:28,760
You seem busier than me
even though I'm in Taereung.

253
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:31,240
I'm busy with training.

254
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:33,600
Lately, I've been busy with many things.

255
00:15:35,160 --> 00:15:36,480
Things like what?

256
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:38,160
What?

257
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:41,880
I'm just saying.

258
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:43,720
What could I be busy with?

259
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:46,880
You're so wishy-washy.

260
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:50,360
Is it because you don't like me anymore?

261
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:54,120
Bok-ju, come here for a minute.

262
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:57,720
Okay, someone is calling me.
I'll call you later.

263
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:00,560
Bok-ju.

264
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:02,960
Chubs

265
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:05,240
We only talked for a minute.

266
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:09,240
I miss you more after hearing your voice.

267
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:19,560
I miss you, Bok-ju.

268
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:23,760
I miss you like crazy, Bok-ju.

269
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:49,840
Let's focus.

270
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:51,960
The competition is coming up.
Let's focus.

271
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:08,960
What's wrong, Bok-ju? Is your back okay?

272
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:11,040
I think I hurt my back.

273
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:14,720
Your back keeps getting in the way.
Your competition is coming up soon.

274
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:16,400
Let me see it.

275
00:17:17,920 --> 00:17:20,480
-Does this hurt?
-It's okay, I can endure the pain.

276
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:22,280
No, it's not good.

277
00:17:22,520 --> 00:17:23,760
You can't continue like this.

278
00:17:23,840 --> 00:17:26,280
It's better that you get treated first.

279
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:29,880
There's a place called
Dr Park's Hospital.

280
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:32,960
They specialise in injuries for
athletes, so go there for treatment.

281
00:17:33,280 --> 00:17:35,560
Get some rest at home,
and come back tomorrow.

282
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:37,240
I give you my permission.

283
00:17:37,520 --> 00:17:39,960
-Are you serious, Coach?
-Yes.

284
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:43,960
You need to get in better shape.
You can't compete with a bad back.

285
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:46,880
Thank you, I'll go get treated.

286
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:49,560
It must go straight up.

287
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:51,120
There it is.

288
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:53,560
It was a success.

289
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:55,400
Oh, Tae-kwon?

290
00:17:55,960 --> 00:17:57,360
What's up, Tae-kwon?

291
00:17:58,440 --> 00:18:01,160
-What are you doing?
-I'm watching competition videos.

292
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:02,720
What is it?

293
00:18:03,120 --> 00:18:05,080
I'm not working today.

294
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:08,800
Do you want to see a movie with me?

295
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:10,680
A movie sounds good. Just a moment.

296
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:13,880
-I'll ask Nan-hee when she's back...
-Wait, don't ask her.

297
00:18:14,840 --> 00:18:16,000
Let's go without her.

298
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:18,360
I want to go with you.

299
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:31,200
Are you surprised
that I asked you out for a movie?

300
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:34,080
No.

301
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:37,080
I think I'm more surprised that
you're talking to me casually now.

302
00:18:38,240 --> 00:18:40,440
Then shall I go back to talking politely?

303
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:42,360
You don't need to do that.

304
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:44,160
I'm sure I'll get used to it soon.

305
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,840
-Hey, guys!
-Gosh.

306
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:57,040
Where were you, Nan-hee? My gosh.

307
00:18:57,120 --> 00:18:58,360
-Hi, Nan-hee.
-Hi.

308
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:00,760
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

309
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:08,480
This doctor is really good.
The tension is gone.

310
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:10,120
Nice. I'm free from the pain now.

311
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:13,200
Would Joon-hyung be done now?

312
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:18,680
I should go home first.

313
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:22,480
Then, I should call Dad.

314
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,520
Hey, Bok-ju.

315
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,160
Hi, Uncle. Where's Dad?

316
00:19:34,560 --> 00:19:36,960
Well, he's in the bathroom.

317
00:19:37,040 --> 00:19:39,160
I think he has diarrhoea or something.

318
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:41,880
Really? What did he eat?

319
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:44,880
Uncle, I got a day off
to get treatment for my lower back.

320
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,880
If I take a taxi,
I can be home in 20 minutes.

321
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:51,120
What did you just say?
You're coming home now?

322
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:57,400
Okay. All right, Bok-ju.
I left something on the stove.

323
00:19:57,480 --> 00:19:59,480
Yes, okay. I have to go. Bye.

324
00:20:02,080 --> 00:20:04,120
What do we do? She's on her way home now.

325
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:07,000
-What if she sees the sign?
-We have no choice.

326
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:09,960
-We should go home now.
-You'll hurt yourself.

327
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:11,480
We're already doomed.

328
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:14,960
She'll be there in 20 minutes.
It'll take at least an hour for us.

329
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:17,280
What should we do, then?
If she finds out,

330
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:19,080
she'll cry her eyes out and go crazy.

331
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:22,160
Hold on. Let's calm down
and try to collect our thoughts.

332
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:25,720
We have to stop her
from going home, right?

333
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:28,400
-What about her friends?
-Right, her friends.

334
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:31,360
-Shall I ask them to snatch her?
-Yes, call them now.

335
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:35,000
-You should use your phone.
-Oh, right. My phone is here.

336
00:20:35,760 --> 00:20:38,360
The seizure procedure has begun. I was...

337
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:40,880
a prosecutor in the Special Crimes Unit.

338
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:44,200
The unit is still filled
with my junior colleagues.

339
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,480
Please trust me...

340
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:50,000
and sign this power of attorney.

341
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:52,280
I promise...

342
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:54,400
you'll get your money back.

343
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:03,080
It's so funny.

344
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:16,960
That's way too light.

345
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:34,200
Hi, Uncle.

346
00:21:34,880 --> 00:21:36,480
I'm at the gym. What's up?

347
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:38,800
Sorry?

348
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:40,720
Bok-ju is what?

349
00:21:41,760 --> 00:21:44,960
My home sweet home, Bok Chicken!

350
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:47,440
Kim Bok-ju is back. I'm home.

351
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:50,480
Bok-ju! Bok-ju, Bok-ju!

352
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:52,440
Joon-hyung!

353
00:21:56,360 --> 00:21:58,840
-How did you know that I'm here?
-What?

354
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:04,080
I didn't know. I was coming here
to eat fried chicken when I saw you.

355
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:07,760
This must be what people call telepathy.

356
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:10,400
We must really be meant to be.

357
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:13,320
It is pretty cool. Let's go in together.

358
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:15,440
Hey! Bok-ju.

359
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:18,600
-I missed you so much.
-What's the matter with you?

360
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:24,480
Hey, did you do something wrong?
Is that why you're acting like this?

361
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:27,680
What are you talking about?
I just missed you so much.

362
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:32,360
Hey, let's go. We should go
eat something delicious.

363
00:22:32,720 --> 00:22:34,440
How about we go for barbecue?

364
00:22:34,800 --> 00:22:36,960
Okay. Let me say a quick hi
to my dad before we go.

365
00:22:37,040 --> 00:22:39,360
Hey! You can do that later.

366
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:42,440
I'm starving right now.
Let's go eat meat. It's on me.

367
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:43,640
Turn around!

368
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:45,680
Go.

369
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,120
Hurry up now.

370
00:22:57,160 --> 00:23:00,440
I'm not sure why I have to eat
fried chicken here,

371
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:04,120
but I guess knowing my enemy
isn't a bad thing. Let's eat.

372
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:06,000
Yes, exactly. Eat up.

373
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:09,280
It looks like you've lost
a bit of weight.

374
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:12,320
-I've gained weight.
-I haven't seen you in so long.

375
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:15,080
How have you been, Chubs?

376
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:16,680
You're asking that just now?

377
00:23:17,240 --> 00:23:19,720
-I've been great. Are we good now?
-Do you have to talk like that?

378
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:22,040
You haven't seen your darling here
in such a long time.

379
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:23,320
My darling? Whatever.

380
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:27,480
Hey, be honest with me.

381
00:23:27,560 --> 00:23:28,960
What are you up to these days?

382
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:32,040
Have you been partying and
hanging out with girls like crazy?

383
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:35,120
Do you think I'm crazy?
I know you'll kill me if I do that.

384
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:37,400
-So you didn't do that?
-Of course not.

385
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:58,360
I have to go to the bathroom.

386
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:11,160
Hello, Uncle. Go ahead.

387
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:13,160
How did it go with Bok-ju?

388
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:16,680
I'm making sure
she can't go anywhere. Don't worry.

389
00:24:16,840 --> 00:24:19,000
My gosh. Thanks so much, Joon-hyung.

390
00:24:19,080 --> 00:24:21,960
I think we'll be home
in about 20 minutes.

391
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:24,520
Stall her for another 30 minutes, okay?

392
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:29,120
Okay, I will. Please don't worry.
I'll do my best to keep Bok-ju here.

393
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:30,960
Please be careful.

394
00:24:34,160 --> 00:24:38,000
Okay, I should go now. All right.

395
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:43,360
Weren't you going to the bathroom?
Why are you taking a call here?

396
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:45,960
I was feeling a little claustrophobic,

397
00:24:46,040 --> 00:24:47,840
so I wanted to get some fresh air.

398
00:24:49,520 --> 00:24:52,640
-Who called you?
-What? It's someone you don't know.

399
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:55,760
Hey, let's go eat.
The chicken will get cold.

400
00:24:55,840 --> 00:24:58,120
Come on. Let's go.

401
00:24:58,520 --> 00:24:59,560
Goodness.

402
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:03,280
Who was it? Why can't you tell me?

403
00:25:03,360 --> 00:25:06,760
It's not that I can't tell you.
It's just someone you don't know.

404
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:10,000
So who is it? I'm sure
that person has a name. Tell me.

405
00:25:10,280 --> 00:25:11,720
You don't know him.

406
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:15,800
His name is Seung-jin.
He's my friend from high school.

407
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:19,560
Friend? Do you usually talk
that politely to your friends?

408
00:25:19,640 --> 00:25:21,440
You must have huge respect for him.

409
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:25,040
Hey, when did I talk like that?

410
00:25:25,360 --> 00:25:27,120
You misheard me.

411
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:30,560
We haven't seen each other forever.
Why are you trying to pick a fight?

412
00:25:30,640 --> 00:25:33,480
It wasn't a friend, right?
It must be a girl.

413
00:25:33,760 --> 00:25:37,280
What are you talking about?
Why are you so suspicious of me?

414
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:39,520
It's because you're acting suspiciously!

415
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:41,560
Give me your phone. Show me his name.

416
00:25:41,720 --> 00:25:42,920
What are you doing now?

417
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:45,560
Goodness gracious.
How dare you glare at me.

418
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:48,600
You're only increasing my suspicion.
Give it to me.

419
00:25:48,680 --> 00:25:51,040
-Stop it.
-You said you did nothing wrong.

420
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:52,280
Show me his name. Give it to me.

421
00:25:52,360 --> 00:25:54,520
What is wrong with you?
Don't you trust me?

422
00:25:57,680 --> 00:25:59,440
Okay. I was out of line.

423
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:03,200
I've been on edge because
of my training. Let's not fight.

424
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:10,160
Yes. Why are you suspicious of me?

425
00:26:10,280 --> 00:26:13,360
I have never even looked at other girls.

426
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:14,600
Trust me.

427
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:21,400
Hey. Hey! Give it back.

428
00:26:21,480 --> 00:26:24,000
-Who is this person?
-Hey, give it back to me now.

429
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:27,880
Hey, stop.

430
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:29,760
Give it back!

431
00:26:30,600 --> 00:26:31,760
Give it back.

432
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:36,960
I know that we're dating, but we
must respect each other's privacy.

433
00:26:37,040 --> 00:26:38,640
Going through your boyfriend's phone...

434
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:41,160
is such a mannerless thing to do.

435
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:43,800
Privacy? Mannerless?

436
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:46,000
Wow! You're so intelligent.

437
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:49,200
I don't know what privacy or manner is,
so I'll just leave you alone.

438
00:26:49,280 --> 00:26:51,400
Have fun with your new girlfriend. Bye!

439
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:54,120
Hey, wait. Hey!

440
00:26:56,760 --> 00:26:57,800
Bok-ju.

441
00:26:58,400 --> 00:26:59,960
Oh, I have to pay.

442
00:27:00,280 --> 00:27:01,720
Hey, Bok-ju. Wait up!

443
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:04,280
What is the matter with you?
It's nothing to get angry about.

444
00:27:04,360 --> 00:27:06,960
Right. I'm getting worked up
over nothing, aren't I?

445
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:10,240
I'm overreacting and have trust issues.
Let's say it's all my fault!

446
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:12,720
Hey, why are you talking like that?

447
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:14,960
We haven't seen each other forever.
Let's make up.

448
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:17,640
Exactly. I didn't want
to be like this, too,

449
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:19,200
but I can't stop feeling angry.

450
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:21,760
My lower back is killing me, but
I was still so excited...

451
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:23,800
to see you and Dad like an idiot!

452
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:26,440
I really didn't think
you'd do this to me.

453
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:28,440
Hey, Kim Bok-ju.

454
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:32,640
Gosh, I can't even tell her the truth.

455
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:37,640
Has it been 30 minutes? Goodness.

456
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,880
He doesn't love me as much anymore.
What a jerk.

457
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:44,600
He used to be so sweet to me.
We weren't even apart for that long.

458
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:48,960
Fine. The world is wide
and there are many pretty girls.

459
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:51,000
What a jerk.

460
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:54,600
Bok Chicken

461
00:27:54,760 --> 00:27:56,920
Dad! Uncle!

462
00:28:03,600 --> 00:28:05,800
-What are you doing, Uncle?
-What?

463
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:08,640
Hey, Bok-ju. You're here.

464
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:12,880
Is your back okay now?
Did you get it treated?

465
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:15,480
I feel much better after going to
the hospital the coach recommended.

466
00:28:15,880 --> 00:28:18,000
Why are you wearing a mask?
Did you catch a cold?

467
00:28:19,160 --> 00:28:21,680
I might give it to the customers.
It's just a prevention.

468
00:28:21,800 --> 00:28:25,120
Be careful, Dad. They say
the flu this winter is really bad.

469
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:29,920
Why are you sweating so much, Uncle?
Did you go somewhere?

470
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:35,480
I think I've become poor in health.
I sweat so much these days.

471
00:28:35,680 --> 00:28:37,600
I guess my andropause started early.

472
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:39,840
You should get married soon.

473
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:41,480
Uncle.

474
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:44,600
-What are you doing?
-It's a prevention.

475
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:46,480
Why are you cleaning
the fire extinguisher?

476
00:28:47,120 --> 00:28:48,200
To prevent fire.

477
00:28:48,280 --> 00:28:50,000
-Bok-ju!
-Bok-ju!

478
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:52,880
What are you doing here, guys?
How did you know I was here?

479
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:56,320
-What's going on?
-We just came to eat chicken...

480
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:58,120
when we heard your voice.

481
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:01,640
We just have telepathic
connections, don't we?

482
00:29:01,720 --> 00:29:03,560
-We're awesome.
-Awesome.

483
00:29:03,760 --> 00:29:04,880
All right.

484
00:29:05,800 --> 00:29:07,680
Why does everyone keep talking
about telepathy?

485
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:09,960
Bok-ju, I missed you.

486
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:12,200
-Did you?
-Welcome back.

487
00:29:12,280 --> 00:29:13,880
You eat chicken without me now.

488
00:29:23,560 --> 00:29:26,240
Dr Go. He's late today.

489
00:29:26,440 --> 00:29:27,760
Maybe he's busy.

490
00:29:27,960 --> 00:29:30,480
I'm not waiting for him.

491
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:32,280
I didn't say you were.

492
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:34,360
Should we go home first?

493
00:29:34,720 --> 00:29:36,880
Of course.
I'm going to go home soon, too.

494
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:39,320
-I just want to see some documents.
-Okay.

495
00:29:51,520 --> 00:29:52,640
Ah-young!

496
00:29:58,600 --> 00:29:59,600
I'm sorry.

497
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:01,720
A seminar suddenly came up.

498
00:30:02,280 --> 00:30:03,800
I came as soon as it ended,

499
00:30:04,360 --> 00:30:05,480
but I'm a little late.

500
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:08,960
I drove really fast
so I wouldn't keep you waiting.

501
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:10,880
I wasn't waiting for you.

502
00:30:11,800 --> 00:30:14,800
-I just had many patients today.
-Is that so?

503
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,400
I guess I was happy over nothing.

504
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,000
Have you had dinner?

505
00:30:20,080 --> 00:30:23,640
Of course. I ate with the nurses.
What time do you think it is now?

506
00:30:23,840 --> 00:30:25,840
You're still going to eat with me, right?

507
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:28,040
I rushed all the way here.

508
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:29,960
All right.

509
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:33,920
You did come all the way here. I can't
tell you to go back without eating.

510
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:36,080
Let's go, then.

511
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:56,680
Here. Eat up.

512
00:30:57,760 --> 00:30:59,160
They make delicious food here.

513
00:31:00,120 --> 00:31:02,560
I couldn't finish my dinner
because I got a patient.

514
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:04,680
I'm sure.

515
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:06,720
Eat up. I didn't say anything.

516
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:12,880
By the way, I think we've been
to almost every restaurant here.

517
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:14,520
Well...

518
00:31:15,080 --> 00:31:16,680
I guess you're right.

519
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:19,440
I wanted to buy you
something more delicious,

520
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:21,320
but I don't know this neighbourhood well.

521
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:24,400
So I searched the Internet
for good restaurants around here.

522
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:25,760
There is...

523
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:28,760
a very famous place that
makes squid bulgogi.

524
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:32,240
There's also a popular samgyetang
restaurant in the suburb.

525
00:31:32,560 --> 00:31:33,680
The drumsticks look good.

526
00:31:35,280 --> 00:31:38,080
We can go for rice with wraps, too.
You like that, right?

527
00:31:38,600 --> 00:31:40,560
Gosh. Look at these pictures.

528
00:31:40,640 --> 00:31:41,800
Look. What do you think?

529
00:31:41,880 --> 00:31:44,360
What do you say we eat it next time?

530
00:31:48,320 --> 00:31:49,480
I should go.

531
00:31:50,720 --> 00:31:53,080
I have some more work to do.
Enjoy your dinner. Bye.

532
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:57,680
Ah-young.

533
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:01,040
Ah-young. Hang on.

534
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:03,960
Here you go.

535
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:06,320
-Please keep the change. Ah-young!
-Thank you.

536
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:08,640
Ah-young, what's wrong?

537
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:11,160
Did I make a mistake again?

538
00:32:12,120 --> 00:32:14,160
Yes. You did.

539
00:32:14,720 --> 00:32:17,920
I moved here to avoid you.
I wanted to be away from you.

540
00:32:18,400 --> 00:32:19,400
But these days,

541
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:22,400
I find myself waiting for you
every evening.

542
00:32:23,280 --> 00:32:26,200
I feel like I'm developing
a crush on you all over again.

543
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:29,000
It scares me and I hate it.

544
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:31,640
So don't come out here again.

545
00:32:32,560 --> 00:32:34,160
I won't eat with you anymore.

546
00:32:42,080 --> 00:32:43,480
A Seoul without you...

547
00:32:44,880 --> 00:32:46,280
is too lonely. I hate it.

548
00:32:49,120 --> 00:32:50,720
So, don't tell me not to come.

549
00:32:57,800 --> 00:32:58,840
What did you...

550
00:32:59,160 --> 00:33:01,560
mean by the things you just said?

551
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:06,040
Do you...

552
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:08,000
like Messi?

553
00:33:13,760 --> 00:33:16,960
That's a lousy way of
proposing to someone.

554
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:19,160
I know.

555
00:33:49,280 --> 00:33:50,680
No, not that.

556
00:33:52,280 --> 00:33:53,880
My goodness. Here.

557
00:33:54,080 --> 00:33:58,080
-Get it yourself. You're so lazy.
-Just eat this.

558
00:33:59,480 --> 00:34:01,200
-I can't reach it.
-Gosh.

559
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:06,120
Who is it? Why aren't you answering?

560
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:08,440
Who is it? Isn't that Joon-hyung?

561
00:34:08,560 --> 00:34:11,280
-Why aren't you answering?
-I don't care. I hate him.

562
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:13,760
What's wrong? You two were madly in love.

563
00:34:13,840 --> 00:34:16,360
-Are you fed up with him already?
-Whatever.

564
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:18,200
I guess all men are the same.

565
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:21,960
The moment you loosen their leash,
they start getting ideas.

566
00:34:22,160 --> 00:34:25,960
Bok Chicken

567
00:34:30,640 --> 00:34:32,640
Gosh. She must be really mad at me.

568
00:34:33,480 --> 00:34:37,480
We don't have much time to be together.
Please pick up already, Bok-ju.

569
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:39,720
The person you're trying to reach
is not available.

570
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:44,240
Bok Chicken

571
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:58,000
What are you doing here?

572
00:34:59,760 --> 00:35:00,920
Hello, Sir.

573
00:35:05,120 --> 00:35:07,320
Why were you waiting outside in the cold?

574
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:09,360
If she didn't pick up,

575
00:35:09,880 --> 00:35:11,160
you should've just gone home.

576
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:13,080
Thank you for the drink.

577
00:35:18,560 --> 00:35:20,040
Are you feeling okay?

578
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:23,000
Of course. It's not like I'm dying.

579
00:35:24,440 --> 00:35:27,200
Why is Bok-ju mad at you?
What did you do?

580
00:35:27,480 --> 00:35:30,800
I didn't do anything. She just
misunderstood about something.

581
00:35:31,360 --> 00:35:33,200
-It's nothing big.
-Is that right?

582
00:35:34,160 --> 00:35:36,960
Anyway, thank you for helping me today.

583
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,720
-Did you say you are a swimmer?
-Yes.

584
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:42,000
How good are you?

585
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:44,400
I won second place
in the last national qualifier.

586
00:35:45,880 --> 00:35:47,600
You should've won the first place.

587
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:52,440
-Do you have both of your parents?
-Yes.

588
00:35:52,800 --> 00:35:55,000
They run a pharmacy together.

589
00:35:57,880 --> 00:35:59,720
They're actually my aunt and uncle.

590
00:36:00,160 --> 00:36:03,480
My dad died when I was little
and my mum remarried,

591
00:36:05,160 --> 00:36:06,960
so I grew up in my uncle's house.

592
00:36:08,760 --> 00:36:12,600
But I've been well-loved by them.
I never felt like anything was missing.

593
00:36:14,520 --> 00:36:17,280
I've never heard someone say
he's been well-loved himself.

594
00:36:18,800 --> 00:36:22,480
By the way, why do you like Bok-ju?

595
00:36:24,200 --> 00:36:25,320
She just...

596
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:28,360
...feels warm.

597
00:36:31,240 --> 00:36:33,560
She's warm with her friends,

598
00:36:34,280 --> 00:36:37,680
when she is with you and her uncle,

599
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:41,880
and also when she lifts weights.

600
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:50,280
Somehow, ever since she was little,
Bok-ju just makes your heart warm.

601
00:36:51,360 --> 00:36:52,480
I guess.

602
00:36:53,520 --> 00:36:56,400
She takes after me
in that she's very friendly.

603
00:36:57,720 --> 00:37:00,920
That's right. Bok-ju is just like you.

604
00:37:03,480 --> 00:37:04,720
Don't laugh, you brat.

605
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:06,480
I know you're lying.

606
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:09,800
You're quite cheeky, you rascal.

607
00:37:16,080 --> 00:37:17,280
Goodness.

608
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:20,800
Bok-ju, hurry up and go.

609
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:23,640
-You're on the national team now.
-I'm going.

610
00:37:23,720 --> 00:37:26,120
Just go already. I hope the rest
of your training goes well.

611
00:37:26,200 --> 00:37:27,520
Watch your back as well.

612
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:29,520
I hope you'll get over your cold soon.

613
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:31,640
Uncle, work harder
and let him rest, okay?

614
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:35,280
I know. Don't worry and just go.
A national athlete shouldn't be late.

615
00:37:35,400 --> 00:37:37,480
Fine, I'm going.
Why are you so eager to send me away?

616
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:40,160
I'll call you. I love you. I love you.

617
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:41,880
Okay. I'll see you later.

618
00:37:44,560 --> 00:37:46,400
-We should hurry.
-Okay.

619
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:53,360
Closed due to personal reasons

620
00:37:53,440 --> 00:37:56,280
I always forget to bring
my extra battery.

621
00:37:58,240 --> 00:38:01,160
What? Why is it closed?

622
00:38:03,280 --> 00:38:05,600
Where did they disappear to so quickly?

623
00:38:08,600 --> 00:38:10,360
Bok-ju, long time no see.

624
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:12,680
-Hello.
-Hello.

625
00:38:12,760 --> 00:38:15,680
I heard you went to Taereung.
Are you visiting home?

626
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:20,160
By the way,
when is your father's surgery?

627
00:38:20,240 --> 00:38:21,760
Pardon? His surgery?

628
00:38:31,200 --> 00:38:34,920
My gosh, it's Bok-ju again.

629
00:38:35,400 --> 00:38:37,000
Why does she keep calling me?

630
00:38:38,640 --> 00:38:40,600
My Bok-ju, did you get back safely?

631
00:38:41,160 --> 00:38:43,280
Where are you right now?

632
00:38:43,640 --> 00:38:46,640
Where else? The restaurant, of course.

633
00:38:46,720 --> 00:38:49,680
Now that you've left again,
it feels so empty here.

634
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:52,080
Really? You're really at the restaurant?

635
00:38:52,240 --> 00:38:54,160
Yes, I am.

636
00:38:56,480 --> 00:38:57,880
Is this the restaurant?

637
00:38:58,560 --> 00:39:00,280
Yes, this is the restaurant.

638
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:03,560
Your voice sounds so clear.

639
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:22,240
I swear. I was going to tell you...

640
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:25,040
right after your competition. Honest.

641
00:39:26,560 --> 00:39:28,840
I told him not to tell you...

642
00:39:29,080 --> 00:39:30,800
...in case you can't focus.

643
00:39:32,280 --> 00:39:34,600
It's your
first international competition.

644
00:39:35,760 --> 00:39:37,480
If you ruin it because of me,

645
00:39:38,120 --> 00:39:40,720
I'd regret it all my life.

646
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:44,080
Don't be angry, Bok-ju.

647
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:46,440
I'm not angry.

648
00:39:48,880 --> 00:39:51,400
When I heard your weak voice...

649
00:39:51,880 --> 00:39:54,840
and saw you wearing a mask,
I should have noticed it.

650
00:39:56,560 --> 00:39:58,560
No matter how much I try to hide it,

651
00:39:58,640 --> 00:40:01,360
you'd know if I'm sick or in a bad mood.

652
00:40:02,640 --> 00:40:04,360
I'm nowhere near that.

653
00:40:04,880 --> 00:40:07,600
That's because I'm your parent.

654
00:40:08,640 --> 00:40:09,640
Dad.

655
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:14,640
I'll do well.

656
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:18,360
I'll win the gold medal
and put it around your neck,

657
00:40:18,560 --> 00:40:21,600
so stay strong and
get through the surgery, okay?

658
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:23,880
I believe in you, Dad.

659
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,560
Yes, believe in me.

660
00:40:27,880 --> 00:40:29,080
Just believe me.

661
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:33,600
If you win the gold medal,

662
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:37,080
you should treat Joon-hyung to a meal.

663
00:40:37,200 --> 00:40:41,120
He helped take care of your dad,
and even stalled you yesterday.

664
00:40:41,680 --> 00:40:42,880
He's done a lot.

665
00:40:47,560 --> 00:40:52,240
Indoor Swimming Pool

666
00:40:58,000 --> 00:41:01,520
Bok-ju, what are you doing here?
Didn't you go back?

667
00:41:03,040 --> 00:41:04,440
I'm very thoughtless.

668
00:41:04,520 --> 00:41:07,080
I'm self-centred
and not understanding at all.

669
00:41:07,160 --> 00:41:09,280
I don't deserve you as my boyfriend.

670
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:13,160
What are you doing?
Have you lost your mind?

671
00:41:14,760 --> 00:41:16,000
I think so.

672
00:41:16,080 --> 00:41:18,800
I believed what my senior athletes
said without proof...

673
00:41:18,880 --> 00:41:21,080
when you have done so much for my dad.

674
00:41:21,600 --> 00:41:23,280
Please hit me. I deserve it.

675
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:25,160
Stop it. It will hurt.

676
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:29,280
I tried to keep it a secret,
but you found out.

677
00:41:29,840 --> 00:41:31,240
I'm really sorry.

678
00:41:32,080 --> 00:41:35,080
I'm worried because you're too handsome.

679
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:37,400
On top of that, you're tall...

680
00:41:37,520 --> 00:41:40,320
and have a great personality
that any woman would fall for.

681
00:41:41,880 --> 00:41:44,080
-What else?
-Your hands are warm,

682
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:46,320
and you're good at swimming and kissing.

683
00:41:47,520 --> 00:41:50,120
-What else?
-There's nothing more.

684
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:54,080
How did you find out? Are things
okay between you and your dad?

685
00:41:56,080 --> 00:41:59,000
Let's go before it gets late.
I'll take you to Taereung.

686
00:42:09,080 --> 00:42:10,800
We're already here.

687
00:42:10,880 --> 00:42:13,680
-I thought Taereung was farther.
-I know.

688
00:42:13,800 --> 00:42:15,920
It seemed far when I travelled alone.

689
00:42:17,560 --> 00:42:19,520
Bok-ju, look at me.

690
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:21,480
Look me in the eyes.

691
00:42:23,720 --> 00:42:25,840
Can you see that I'm completely into you?

692
00:42:26,400 --> 00:42:30,080
I don't know about a million years
from now, but I won't cheat on you now.

693
00:42:30,520 --> 00:42:32,920
Don't worry and
focus on your training, okay?

694
00:42:34,680 --> 00:42:36,400
Don't worry about your dad's surgery.

695
00:42:36,520 --> 00:42:40,040
I'll stay with him and
do my best to take care of him...

696
00:42:40,280 --> 00:42:42,000
...as if I were you.

697
00:42:44,720 --> 00:42:45,800
Do you trust me?

698
00:42:47,120 --> 00:42:48,280
Yes, I do.

699
00:42:49,640 --> 00:42:50,800
Okay, go in.

700
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:54,800
Concentrate only on your training
and nothing else, okay?

701
00:42:55,600 --> 00:42:58,400
You better win the gold medal.
Otherwise...

702
00:42:59,080 --> 00:43:01,240
-Otherwise?
-I'll hug you.

703
00:43:02,640 --> 00:43:05,840
Don't feel pressured.
There will always be another chance.

704
00:43:06,680 --> 00:43:08,800
Okay, you should leave first.

705
00:43:09,080 --> 00:43:10,600
No, you go in first.

706
00:43:11,040 --> 00:43:13,640
-Come on, you leave first.
-No, you go in first.

707
00:43:16,760 --> 00:43:17,760
Go.

708
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:22,480
Go on.

709
00:43:23,880 --> 00:43:25,800
What are you doing? Go.

710
00:43:30,680 --> 00:43:31,880
See you.

711
00:43:32,840 --> 00:43:34,040
Go on.

712
00:43:38,440 --> 00:43:39,640
See you.

713
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:57,280
See you.

714
00:44:00,880 --> 00:44:04,280
Breathe, and get ready.

715
00:44:07,200 --> 00:44:08,880
That was good this time.

716
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:11,280
Pay attention to your legs.

717
00:44:12,280 --> 00:44:14,360
That's right. Hold it. Good job.

718
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:15,960
Bok-ju.

719
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:19,600
Sausages at the convenience store
remind me of you.

720
00:44:20,640 --> 00:44:23,840
I broke my unofficial records today.
I'll catch up to you soon.

721
00:44:24,280 --> 00:44:26,600
Work hard today.
You don't have to respond.

722
00:44:28,520 --> 00:44:30,600
How to make salt compress for back pain.

723
00:44:31,160 --> 00:44:32,800
Wrap roasted salt in a towel.

724
00:44:32,880 --> 00:44:34,880
Apply on affected areas
for 30 minutes twice a day.

725
00:44:34,960 --> 00:44:36,920
It's more effective than heat pads.

726
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:40,960
Bok-ju, your dad is in good condition.

727
00:44:41,600 --> 00:44:43,280
He'll get the surgery as scheduled.

728
00:44:44,640 --> 00:44:48,200
There's only one day left to D-Day.
I'll make a wish on your behalf.

729
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:56,440
The World Weightlifting Championship

730
00:45:09,760 --> 00:45:11,880
-If you're ready, let's go.
-Okay.

731
00:45:24,000 --> 00:45:26,880
Bok-ju, you can do this.

732
00:45:27,760 --> 00:45:29,680
You're not alone right now.

733
00:45:30,480 --> 00:45:34,280
There are many people who love you
and cheer for you.

734
00:45:35,360 --> 00:45:36,480
Don't be nervous.

735
00:45:37,080 --> 00:45:38,800
Keep up what you've been doing.

736
00:45:39,640 --> 00:45:41,840
No matter what anyone says,
you'll be a world champion.

737
00:45:42,760 --> 00:45:43,960
Kim Bok-ju.

738
00:45:44,760 --> 00:45:48,360
You can do it. It'll come true.
Let's do it.

739
00:45:53,040 --> 00:45:56,320
Operation Centre

740
00:45:56,400 --> 00:46:00,200
Operation Room

741
00:46:07,800 --> 00:46:10,000
The surgery went well.

742
00:46:10,160 --> 00:46:11,880
His vital signs are normal.

743
00:46:11,960 --> 00:46:15,120
We'll transfer him to the recovery
room and keep an eye on him.

744
00:46:15,200 --> 00:46:17,320
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

745
00:46:18,760 --> 00:46:19,960
Thank you, Doctor.

746
00:46:20,360 --> 00:46:22,360
When does the championship start?

747
00:46:24,880 --> 00:46:26,040
It's starting soon.

748
00:46:44,280 --> 00:46:45,480
Clean and Jerk.

749
00:46:45,840 --> 00:46:46,920
There's Bok-ju.

750
00:46:47,000 --> 00:46:49,800
-Bok-ju, you can do it.
-Let's go, Bok-ju.

751
00:46:49,880 --> 00:46:51,200
Republic of Korea.

752
00:46:52,040 --> 00:46:53,440
Kim Bok-ju.

753
00:46:54,240 --> 00:46:55,560
Third attempt.

754
00:47:33,720 --> 00:47:34,920
Please.

755
00:48:04,600 --> 00:48:06,720
She did it.

756
00:48:10,160 --> 00:48:11,560
That means she won, right?

757
